fields.description:
Most import failures result in a DataSetupException which leads the instance to be Johnsoned. But in case of a failure in the JIRA DataImport action (which we delegate to from StudioImport), we attempt to return an ERROR status from the StudioImport action. The Velocity template intended to handle this scenario fails to render.

For example, here we attempt to import data pointing to non-existent directories for indexes and attachments:

{noformat}
@400000004dfed0e03747061c 2011-06-20 14:47:18,927 TP-Processor7 ERROR sysadmin 886x485x1 11wkixp 59.167.133.3,59.167.133.65 /secure/admin/StudioImport!import.jspa [jira.studio.importer.StudioImport] JIRA import failed
@400000004dfed0e037488cbc 2011-06-20 14:47:18,927 TP-Processor7 ERROR sysadmin 886x485x1 11wkixp 59.167.133.3,59.167.133.65 /secure/admin/StudioImport!import.jspa [jira.studio.importer.StudioImport] The index path /tmp/jira/indexes specified in the backup file is not valid.
@400000004dfed0e037494454 2011-06-20 14:47:18,927 TP-Processor7 ERROR sysadmin 886x485x1 11wkixp 59.167.133.3,59.167.133.65 /secure/admin/StudioImport!import.jspa [jira.studio.importer.StudioImport] The attachment path /tmp/jira/attachments specified in the backup file is not valid.
